  "prompt": "I'm hungry what should I do?",
  "response": "I'm sorry you're feeling hungry! Here are a few options you might consider:\n\n1. **Cook at Home:**\n   - **Check Your Pantry:** Look for ingredients you already have and prepare a simple meal.\n   - **Quick Recipes:** Here are some easy ideas:\n     - **Sandwich or Wrap:** Use bread or tortillas with your favorite fillings.\n     - **Pasta:** Boil some pasta and add a sauce or vegetables.\n     - **Omelette:** Eggs are versatile and can be cooked with various add-ins.\n     - **Salad:** Combine fresh vegetables, proteins like chicken or beans, and a tasty dressing.\n\n2. **Order Takeout or Delivery:**\n   - **Use Delivery Apps:** Platforms like Uber Eats, DoorDash, Grubhub, or Deliveroo can bring your favorite meals right to your door.\n   - **Call Local Restaurants:** Support nearby eateries by ordering directly from them.\n\n3. **Grab a Snack:**\n   - If you're not looking for a full meal, a healthy snack like fruit, nuts, yogurt, or a granola bar can help tide you over until your next meal.\n\n4. **Visit a Nearby Restaurant or Caf\u00e9:**\n   - If you feel like going out, find a nearby place that offers the type of food you're craving.\n\n5. **Meal Planning:**\n   - If you often find yourself hungry, consider planning your meals ahead of time to ensure you have nutritious options available.\n\nIf you need specific recipe ideas or have any dietary preferences, feel free to let me know, and I can provide more tailored suggestions!",
